modules.description: This module provides migration annotations to adapt Stdlib functions to their equivalents in Base, specifically for functions operating on compatible data types like `String`, `List`, and `Option`. It enables direct replacement of Stdlib calls with Base equivalents without altering the underlying data structures. Use this when transitioning existing codebases from Stdlib to Base while ensuring type compatibility.

This module provides attributes to migrate code from older Stdlib names to preferred modern equivalents, such as replacing `acos` with `Float.acos`. It works with OCaml source code identifiers and compiler attributes. Use it to automatically rewrite deprecated function names during compilation.
